                                            "text": "One of the saddest aspects of the increasing civil unrest in the US is that leadership in both ruling political parties could end this if they wanted but they specifically choose not to in order to cement power and control for personal gain. The vast majority of the country agrees on a common sense approach that involves policing criminals and not shooting American protesters but the political ruling class prefers a divided society where individuals are pitted against each other, rather than against the system. This is no longer left vs. right, but rather class warfare - elite/wealthy/powerful vs. citizens. Over time this is becoming better understood by the general public and the populist heat will continue to rise and be increasingly directed towards politicians and leadership who own accountability for outcomes as the elected officials in charge.",
